# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __rtruediv__, __rfloordiv__, __rmod__ across all 6 decimal subjects
#
# 6 classes x 3 methods = 18 rows.
# decimal.Decimal defines all three reflected division/modulo operators (true x3);
# all other decimal classes define none (false x15).
# Decimal is a complete numeric type supporting right-hand arithmetic with
# mixed operands (e.g. int / Decimal); Context and exception subclasses are
# not numeric operands and define no reflected arithmetic in their own __dict__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

